  "body": "Hello, i'm trying to make a validator for forms, and i want to make possible of usage LinkedStateMixin with the validator. So, for inputs validation i use native events (addEventListener), for it, i make following actions (it's just an approximate algorithm)\n\n```\n<input valueLink={linkState('input1')}\n           ref={(node)=>{this.inputs.push(node)}}/>\n<select name=\"selectValue\"\n        ref={(node)=>{this.inputs.push(node)}}\n        valueLink={this.linkState('selectValue')}>\n                {['', '1', '2', '3', '4', '5'].map((item)=> {\n                    return <option key={item} value={item}>{item}</option>\n                })}\n</select>\n```\n\n```\ncomponentDidMount(){\n    this.inputs.forEach((node)=>{node.addEventListener...});\n}\n```\n\nIn event handlers (change, blur, keyup) code i perform setState method, if valid state is chaged. With _input_ tag it works very fine, value of state.input1 was changed as expected, but for _select_ tag state.selectValue was changed only one time. So, it's the problem. And i think, this is an issue.\n\nIs it possible at all to make such things work, or i am in the wrong way? I have some Jest tests, i can share it, if needed.\n",
